By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) â€“  The arrested former chairman of the Pension Reform Task Team (PRTT), Abdulrashid  Maina is in detention in Niamey, Niger Republic, and will be extradited upon completion of processes to enable him face trial in pending criminal proceedings against him.Abdulrashid Maina, who was declared wanted by a court of competent jurisdiction, was arrested last night, 30th November 2020 through the collaborative efforts of the operatives of the Nigeria Police Force, INTERPOL NCB, Abuja and their Nigerien counterpart. A statement released by the spokesperson of the Nigeria Police Force NPF, Frank Mba, says Maina is currently in a detention facility in Niger Republic awaiting the completion of the extradition processes.